<div class="container">
  <h2 id="purpose" class="section-title">Purpose & Roles</h2>
  <p>This folder structure standardizes purchasing documentation, reduces errors, and ensures compliance.
     It is maintained primarily by the Purchasing Coordinator but used by multiple roles.</p>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Role</th><th>Responsibility</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Purchasing Coordinator</td><td>Maintain folder integrity, templates, and purchasing documentation.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Project Manager</td><td>Ensure project-specific data is correctly stored.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Accounting</td><td>Manage invoices, payments, and reconciliation files.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Field Supervisors</td><td>Submit receipts and site purchase records.</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2 id="structure" class="section-title">Folder Structure & Examples</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Administration
      <ul><li>Templates & Forms</li><li>Policies & Procedures</li><li>Vendor Management</li></ul>
    </li>
    <li>Projects (Jobs)
      <ul><li>Purchase Orders</li><li>Quotes & Estimates</li><li>Invoices & Receipts</li>
          <li>Subcontracts & Agreements</li><li>Drawings & Specs</li></ul>
    </li>
    <li>Vendors & Suppliers
      <ul><li>Contracts</li><li>Price Lists</li><li>Delivery Schedules</li></ul>
    </li>
    <li>Financial Tracking
      <ul><li>Budgets</li><li>Job Costing</li><li>Reports & Reconciliations</li></ul>
    </li>
    <li>Archives
      <ul><li>Completed Projects</li><li>Inactive Vendors</li></ul>
    </li>
    <li>Personal Tools
      <ul><li>Reference Material</li><li>Macro & Script Tools</li><li>Quick Reference Screenshots</li></ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Document Type</th><th>Example</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Purchase Order</td><td>2025-07-23-PO-ABC_Lumber.pdf</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Vendor Contract</td><td>VendorName-Contract-2025.pdf</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Invoice</td><td>Invoice-ABC_Lumber-2025-07-23.pdf</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Drawing</td><td>ProjectName-Section-Detail#-v1.pdf</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Policy Document</td><td>SOP-Purchasing-2025.pdf</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2 id="workflow" class="section-title">Workflow & Security</h2>
  <p><strong>Workflow Example:</strong> Request → Purchasing Coordinator → Vendor Selection → PO Creation → Accounting → Archiving</p>
  <p><strong>Data Security & Backup Tips:</strong> Use company-managed cloud storage, enable version history, schedule weekly backups, and restrict template editing rights.</p>

  <h2 id="dosdonts" class="section-title">Do's & Don'ts</h2>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Do's</th><th>Don'ts</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Use standardized file names</td><td>Store files outside designated folders</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Archive completed projects promptly</td><td>Keep outdated templates active</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Restrict edit access on core templates</td><td>Ignore backups or versioning</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Ensure receipts are scanned promptly</td><td>Rely only on local machine storage</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2 id="glossary" class="section-title">Glossary & Notes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>PO – Purchase Order</li>
    <li>RFI – Request for Information</li>
    <li>SOP – Standard Operating Procedure</li>
    <li>CO – Change Order</li>
    <li>RFQ – Request for Quotation</li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Change Log Template:</strong></p>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Date</th><th>Description of Change</th><th>Changed By</th></tr>
    <tr><td>YYYY-MM-DD</td><td>Added Vendors folder detail</td><td>Your Name</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h2 id="quickref" class="section-title">Quick Reference</h2>
  <p>A one-page snapshot of folder hierarchy, workflow, and best practices.</p>
</div>

